<div class=3D"paragraph" style=3D"text-align:justify;">The Affine Cipher is=
 another example of a Monoalphabetic Substituiton cipher. It is slightly di=
fferent to the other examples encountered here, since the encryption proces=
s is substantially mathematical. The whole process relies on working <em>mo=
dulo</em> <em>m</em> (the length of the alphabet used). By performing a cal=
culation on the plaintext letters, we encipher the plaintext.</div>

<div><div id=3D"468290890817242432" align=3D"left" style=3D"width: 100%; ov=
erflow-y: hidden;" class=3D"wcustomhtml"><a id=3D"encrypt"></a></div>



</div>

